The paper discusses the technical solutions for coordinated multipoint (CoMP) in 5G systems, which involves network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses key performance indicators (KPIs) and key quality indicators (KQIs) in 5G, which are related to information theory and communication systems, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also mentions empirical measurements and field tests, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.AR (Augmented Reality and Virtual Reality). Finally, the paper proposes a new CoMP architecture, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
